fields: Which teeth are the simplest / least variable?
The {{c1::central}} mandibular incisors are {{c2::slightly smaller}} than the {{c1::lateral}} mandibular incisors.
The {{c1::M-D::M-D or I-C}} is narrower than the {{c1::I-C::M-D or I-C}} in mandibular incisors.
The mandibular incisors have {{c1::three::how many?}} mamelons each.
What universal tooth number accounts for the mandibular central incisors?
What is unique about the mandibular central incisors?
They have the narrowest M-D width and smallest crown size of all teeth.
T/F The mandibular central incisors have a very symmetrical crown.
What is the developmental timeline for madibular central incisors: Initial calcification, Enamel complete, eruption, and root completion.

Initial calcification: 3-4 months 
enamel completion: 4-5 years 
Eruption: 6-7 years 
Root completion: 9 years
The {{c1::incisal 2/3}} of the facial surface of a mandibular central incisor is {{c2::generally flat to slightly convex}}.
Where is the height of contour on a mandibular central incisor?
The geometric form of a mandibular central incisor from a facial viewpoint is {{c1::trapezoidal}}.
The {{c1::mesial}} outline of a mandibular central incsior has an even straight taper towards the cervical end.
The mesial HOC of a mandibular central incisor is at the {{c1::incisal 1/3}}.
The distal outline of a mandibular central incisor is {{c1::almost a mirror image of the mesial outline::compare to mesial outline }}
The incisal outline of a mandibular central incisor is {{c1::perpendicular}} to the long axis.
How many teeth does the mandibular central incisor oppose?
one tooth-- the maxillary central incisor
How many wear facets can you see on a mandibular central incisor?
Only one wear facet because the mandibular central incisors only oppose one maxillary tooth
Describe the lingual view of a mandibular central incisor?
The surface is relatively smooth, marginal ridges are indistict, lingual fossa is shallow, and there are no pits or grooves, a diminshed cingulum.
Where is the height of contour on the ligual surface of a mandibular central incisor?
T/F The mesical CE line curvature of the mandibular later incisor is bigger than the distal line.
The root of the lateral mandibular incisor is thinner than the mandibular central incisor, or is it wider?
The only incisors that can be occasionally bifurcated
Is the distal corner of incisal edge of mandibular lateral incisor twisted facially or lingually?
How many wear facets on teeth 23,26?
The {{c1::DI::DI/MI}} corner of mandibular lateral incisor is slightly {{c2::more::more/less}} rounded.
The cingulum of the mandibular lateral incisor is slightly offset to the {{c1::distal::distal/mesial}}.
